President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri of Adamawa State over the transition of his mother, Hajiya Fatima Umaru Badami, at the age of 68. While commiserating with the family of the governor, the government and people of the state, the president in a statement issued by his media aide, Garba Shehu, said that he received the sad news with shock. Buhari enjoined Governor Fintiri and all those who mourn Hajiya Fatima to be consoled by the knowledge that “she lived a godly life devoted to service to her immediate community and the less-privileged in the society.” He prayed God to give solace to the mourners and accept the soul of Hajiya Fatima. Also, former vice president, Atiku Abubakar, has expressed deepest condolences to the governor over the loss of his mother. According to a statement issued by the Atiku Media Office, the Waziri Adamawa who had earlier spoken to Fintiri over the telephone, acknowledged that “every death diminishes our humanity, but that there can be no loss like that of a mother.”  He noted the role of Hajiya Umaru in shaping Fintiri into who he is just as he counseled the governor to take solace in the fact that his mother lived a fruitful and rewarding life as a community leader and devout Muslim.  Meanwhile, the national leadership of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has condoled with Fintiri over the death of his mother after a protracted illness. A statement issued by the PDP national publicity secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan, said  that the death of Hajiya Badami at this time, was saddening and a painful loss not only to the governor and his immediate family but also to the people of Adamawa State, the country and the PDP as a family. “Hajiya Badami was a devout Muslim; a very kind, humble and generous soul, who devoted her life towards the service of the Almighty Allah and the good of humanity to the very end, despite her protracted health challenges,” the PDP said. 